  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nNA\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n`master`\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nWhen starting boot nodes prior to genesis (i.e., before a new testnet starts), we use `lcli generate-bootnode-enr` to create the `network/` dir with keys, ENR, etc.\r\n\r\nThis works well, however there is a conflict between this line (specifically `EnrForkId::default()`):\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/3b5da8f35f1788972a205af3063a1f1448082d75/lcli/src/generate_bootnode_enr.rs#L33\r\n\r\nAnd this section of [the spec](https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/v0.12.2/specs/phase0/p2p-interface.md#attestation-subnet-bitfield):\r\n\r\n> One notable exception to this rule is the distribution of bootnode ENRs prior to genesis. In this case, bootnode ENRs SHOULD be initially distributed with eth2 field set as ENRForkID(fork_digest=compute_fork_digest(GENESIS_FORK_VERSION, b'\\x00'*32), next_fork_version=GENESIS_FORK_VERSION, next_fork_epoch=FAR_FUTURE_EPOCH). After genesis values are known, the bootnodes SHOULD update ENRs to participate in normal discovery operations.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nEnsure that `generate_bootnode_enr.rs` creates the `EnrForkId` in a way that is faithful to specification before genesis is known.\r\n",
